It depends on, and in some deployment modes bundles, third-party open-source
software, each distributed under its own license. The authoritative inventory of
those components and their licenses is the dependency manifests in this repo:

  - Go modules:   backend/go.mod, backend/go.sum
  - npm packages: frontend/package.json, frontend/package-lock.json

Notable third-party components used at runtime (refer to each project for its
full license text):

  - PostgreSQL with the Apache AGE graph extension. For production, bring your own
    managed instance instead of the bundled demo image.
  - NATS server (event bus).
  - nginx (serves the dashboard's static assets).

No third-party code included in this repository has been modified in a way that
alters its original license terms.
